ie\n* [[Rob Delaney]] as DuBros\n* [[Pallavi Sharda]] as Preeta\n* Jordan Bolger as Cameron\n* [[Patsy Ferran]]\n\n==Production==\nIn October 2018, it was announced that [[Tim Story]] would direct a live-action/animated ''[[Tom and Jerry]]'' film for [[Warner Bros.]], which would begin filming in 2019. It was reported that Story was in discussions with Warner Bros. executives about what he was interested in directing. When the ''Tom and Jerry'' film was brought up, Story immediately \"mentioned his admiration for the characters and how he\u2019d love tackling that property.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Kroll|first=Justin|title=\u2018Tom and Jerry,\u2019 \u2018Scooby-Doo\u2019 Movies Land Top Filmmaking Talent at Warner Animation (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/tom-and-jerry-scooby-doo-tim-story-warner-animation-1202978052/|accessdate=October 16, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=October 15, 2018}}</ref> In March 2019, it was reported that [[Zoey Deutch]] and [[Olivia Cooke]] were frontrunners for the lead live-action role of Kayla, \u201cwho teams up with Tom to stop the pesky Jerry from ruining an important event for herself.\u201d Additionally, [[Yara Shahidi]], [[Kelly Marie Tran]], [[Becky G]] and [[Isabela Moner]] were in consideration for the role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thathashtagshow.com/2019/03/07/exclusive-warner-bros-interested-in-zoey-deutch-and-olivia-cooke-for-a-role-in-the-live-action-tom-and-jerry-film/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Warner Bros. Interested In Zoey Deutch And Olivia Cooke For A Role In The Live-Action 'TOM and JERRY' Film|last=Shuler|first=Skyler|date=March 8, 2019|website=That Hashtag Show|accessdate=March 10, 2019}}</ref> Later that month, it was reported that [[Peter Dinklage]] was being considered for the role of Terrance, Kayla's boss and the human antagonist of the film.<ref>[https://thegww.com/tim-storys-tom-and-jerry-eyeing-peter-dinklage-for-antagonist-role/ TIM STORY\u2019S \u2018TOM AND JERRY\u2019 EYEIN